# Long-Run Autonomy Control Plane

Use this reference when a VibeOS project is expected to run autonomously for 24-48 hours.

## Core Principle

Long-run autonomy is not a promise that one model context will stay alive forever. It is a resumable operating protocol: every loop records state, evidence, next action, and stop conditions so Claude, Codex, or a later session can continue without losing the thread.

## Required Runtime State

| Artifact | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `.vibeos/config.json` | Stores long-run policy, cadence, and stop conditions |
| `.vibeos/session-state.json` | Stores active run id, current WO, iteration, heartbeat, checkpoint, and audit timestamps |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/heartbeats/*.json` | Durable heartbeat evidence for each loop |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/run-lease.json` | Active lease for the current autonomy driver |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/last-lease.json` | Last acquired and released lease evidence |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/lease-conflict.json` | Latest blocked concurrent driver attempt |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/loop-state.json` | Latest scheduler-safe loop tick state |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/loop-history.jsonl` | Append-only loop tick history for stuck-loop detection |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/resume-plan.json` | Supervisor decision and next command plan |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/runner-report.json` | Runner classification, execution, blocked-command, and handoff report |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/runtime-adapter-plan.json` | Planned or executed Codex/Claude runtime handoff command |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/runtime-adapter-history.jsonl` | Append-only runtime handoff history for repeated failure detection |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/failure-report.json` | Failure detector report for loops, blocked runners, lease conflicts, and provider/session limits |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/recovery-plan.json` | Plan-only recovery actions for detected autonomy failures |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/recovery-resolution.json` | Evidence-backed resolution state for recovery-plan actions |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/recovery-resolution-history.jsonl` | Append-only history of recorded recovery resolutions |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/scheduler-guard-report.json` | Pre-tick guard report that blocks unresolved recovery loops |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/scheduler-profile.json` | Generated scheduler profile manifest |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/smoke-report.json` | Disposable autonomy smoke-test report |
| `.vibeos/autonomy/supervisor-state.json` | Latest supervisor decision summary |
| `.vibeos/checkpoints/WO-*.json` | Mid-WO resume state |
| `.vibeos/build-log.md` | Plain chronological event log |
| `.vibeos/session-audits/` | Long-run closeout and periodic audit reports |

## Default Policy

| Control | Default |
|---|---|
| Target duration | 24 hours |
| Hard maximum | 48 hours |
| Heartbeat cadence | Every 30 minutes or after every material loop step |
| Checkpoint cadence | Every 60 minutes or after each agent/work package boundary |
| Audit cadence | Every 180 minutes or at each phase boundary |
| Supervisor poll cadence | Every 15 minutes or after every material tool/runtime boundary |
| Loop iteration ceiling | 512 loop decisions before forced review |
| Failure detector repeat threshold | 3 repeated no-progress loop outcomes |
| Failure detector consecutive failure threshold | 2 consecutive blocked or failed control-plane attempts |
| Recovery planner default | Plan-only actions; no automatic provider launch or lease cleanup |
| Recovery resolution default | Evidence-backed action resolution bound to the current recovery plan generation |
| Scheduler guard default | Block loop ticks while recovery-plan actions lack matching resolution evidence |
| Loop entrypoint default | One scheduler-safe tick; no sleeping unless explicitly requested |
| Loop lease TTL | 30 minutes by default |
| Runtime adapter lease TTL | 6 hours by default |
| Runner default | Dry-run classification; execute only with `--execute` |
| Runtime adapter default | Dry-run handoff plan; launch only with `--execute` |
| Scheduler profile default | Generate reviewed profile files only; do not install system jobs |
| Smoke test default | Disposable target; no model runtime launch |
| Human update cadence | Only at real blockers, explicit risk decisions, phase closeout, or user-requested status |

## Mandatory Stop Conditions

Autonomous mode must pause or stop when any of these happen:

- Security, secret, privacy, or credential risk appears
- Destructive or irreversible action would be required
- Product objective or user-flow intent is unclear
- Gates or audits fail repeatedly after the configured retry ceiling
- Provider/session limit, context exhaustion, tool failure, or runtime launch failure appears
- Repeated handoff, repeated lease conflict, or repeated no-progress loop appears
- The plan is complete or no eligible Work Order remains

## Long-Run Loop

1. Refresh runtime capabilities.
2. Select the next eligible Work Order.
3. Record or refresh `.vibeos/session-state.json`.
4. For scheduler-driven operation, run `.vibeos/scripts/autonomy-scheduler-guard.py` before another tick.
5. Run one `.vibeos/scripts/autonomy-loop.py` tick only when the scheduler guard passes.
6. Otherwise, ask `.vibeos/scripts/autonomy-supervisor.py` for the next action.
7. Classify the supervisor plan with `.vibeos/scripts/autonomy-runner.py`.
8. Execute only allowlisted local VibeOS script commands with `--execute`; treat Codex/Claude continuation text as handoff-required model work.
9. Record a heartbeat with `.vibeos/scripts/autonomy-heartbeat.py` when the supervisor asks for it.
10. Run `.vibeos/scripts/autonomy-failure-detector.py` when a scheduler, adapter, runner, or handoff path repeats.
11. If failures are detected, run `.vibeos/scripts/autonomy-recovery-planner.py`.
12. Record evidence-backed action resolution with `.vibeos/scripts/autonomy-recovery-resolution.py` before scheduling another tick.
13. Execute the next build/audit step.
14. Save a checkpoint after every agent, work package, or material state change.
15. Run gates at WO and phase boundaries.
16. Run session or checkpoint audits on cadence.
17. Record the next heartbeat with the next action.
18. Continue until a mandatory stop condition or plan completion.

## Loop Entrypoint

`autonomy-loop.py` is the scheduler-friendly wrapper around the supervisor and runner. By default it runs one tick, writes `.vibeos/autonomy/loop-state.json`, and exits. With `--execute`, it lets the runner execute only allowlisted local VibeOS scripts. When model continuation is required, it reports `handoff_required` instead of pretending a shell script can perform Codex or Claude reasoning.

## Run Leases

`autonomy-loop.py` and `autonomy-runtime-adapter.py` both acquire `.vibeos/autonomy/run-lease.json` before mutating long-run control state. If another driver owns a live lease, the new driver exits with `lease_conflict` and writes `.vibeos/autonomy/lease-conflict.json`. Expired leases are recovered automatically and recorded in `.vibeos/autonomy/last-lease.json`.

## Runtime Adapter

`autonomy-runtime-adapter.py` reads `.vibeos/runtime-capabilities.json`, `.vibeos/autonomy/loop-state.json`, and `.vibeos/autonomy/runner-report.json`, then writes a Codex or Claude handoff plan to `.vibeos/autonomy/runtime-adapter-plan.json`. It is dry-run by default. With `--execute`, it launches the selected local runtime using stdin prompt handoff and captures the result in the adapter plan.

## Failure Detector

`autonomy-failure-detector.py` reads loop history, runtime-adapter history, runner reports, runtime adapter reports, and lease conflicts, then writes `.vibeos/autonomy/failure-report.json`. It fails only on operational issues: repeated handoff loops, repeated no-progress decisions, consecutive blocked/failed control-plane attempts, active lease conflicts, blocked runners, failed runtime launches, and provider/session limit signals. It is not a token, cost, or elapsed-time budget gate.

## Recovery Planner

`autonomy-recovery-planner.py` reads `.vibeos/autonomy/failure-report.json` and writes `.vibeos/autonomy/recovery-plan.json`. It maps each blocking issue class to a plan-only response: runtime handoff, no-progress inspection, scheduler pause, lease conflict resolution, resume-plan repair, runtime capability refresh, or fresh provider/session resume. It does not clear leases, install schedulers, or launch providers automatically.

## Recovery Resolution

`autonomy-recovery-resolution.py` records evidence that a specific recovery-plan action has been resolved. Resolutions are bound to the current `recovery-plan.json` generation, require a non-empty summary and evidence, write `.vibeos/autonomy/recovery-resolution.json`, and append `.vibeos/autonomy/recovery-resolution-history.jsonl`. It does not edit or clear the recovery plan; it supplies the evidence the scheduler guard needs to unblock the next tick.

## Scheduler Guard

`autonomy-scheduler-guard.py` reads `.vibeos/autonomy/recovery-plan.json` and `.vibeos/autonomy/recovery-resolution.json`, then writes `.vibeos/autonomy/scheduler-guard-report.json`. It exits blocked when recovery actions lack matching resolution evidence for the current recovery plan generation, or when a blocking failure report exists without a recovery plan. Generated scheduler profiles call it before the loop tick, and `autonomy-loop.py` also blocks directly unless invoked with `--ignore-scheduler-guard` for reviewed recovery work.

## Scheduler Profiles And Smoke

`autonomy-scheduler-profile.py` generates shell, cron, launchd, and GitHub Actions profile files under `.vibeos/autonomy/scheduler/`. It does not install them into the operating system or CI provider. `autonomy-smoke.py` creates or uses a disposable target and runs the heartbeat, loop, runtime-adapter planning, validation, failure-detector, recovery-planner, recovery-resolution, and scheduler-guard path before a scheduler profile is installed.

## Runner Safety

`autonomy-runner.py` is intentionally not a general shell runner. It only executes allowlisted VibeOS scripts directly under `.vibeos/scripts` and reports all model-continuation instructions as handoff-required work. It writes `.vibeos/autonomy/runner-report.json` so a reviewer can see what was executed, skipped, blocked, or handed back to the active runtime.

## Reviewer Standard

A 24-48 hour autonomous run is not credible unless a reviewer can answer:

- What was the system trying to accomplish?
- What was active at each heartbeat?
- What did it complete?
- What did it defer?
- Which gates and audits ran?
- What failed, what was retried, and what stopped the run?
- Can another runtime resume from the last heartbeat and checkpoint?

## Commands

```bash
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-heartbeat.py" --status running --summary "starting loop" --next-action "select next WO"
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-heartbeat.py" --status checkpoint --summary "WO checkpoint saved"
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-loop.py" --project-dir "." --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-loop.py" --project-dir "." --execute --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-loop.py" --project-dir "." --lease-owner "scheduler-1" --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-runtime-adapter.py" --project-dir "." --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-runtime-adapter.py" --project-dir "." --provider codex --execute --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-failure-detector.py" --project-dir "." --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-recovery-planner.py" --project-dir "." --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-recovery-resolution.py" --project-dir "." --action-id "RECOVERY-RUNTIME-HANDOFF" --summary "runtime handoff completed" --evidence ".vibeos/autonomy/runtime-adapter-plan.json" --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-scheduler-guard.py" --project-dir "." --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-scheduler-profile.py" --project-dir "." --profile all --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-smoke.py" --runtime-provider codex --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-supervisor.py" --project-dir "." --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-runner.py" --project-dir "." --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/autonomy-runner.py" --project-dir "." --execute --json
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/validate-long-run-autonomy.py" --project-dir "."
python3 ".vibeos/scripts/validate-long-run-autonomy.py" --project-dir "." --require-closed
```
